headline: 'Year-End Pop' in Stocks Could Happen: Schwab's Sonders
summary: Charles Schwab Chief Investment Strategist Liz Ann Sonders says a year-end "pop" in stocks is not out of the question. Speaking with Matt Miller on "Bloomberg Open Interest," Sonders also says she's not ruling out a Federal Reserve rate cute in December.

headline: Schwab Plans to Charge for Shelf Space Next Year. It Could Hit Small Issuers Hardest
summary: Asset managers acknowledge the reality of paying to access Schwab customers, as they have started to do with Fidelity.

headline: 2 of Wall Street’s Favorite Stocks on Our Watchlist and 1 Facing Headwinds
summary: Wall Street is overwhelmingly bullish on the stocks in this article, with price targets suggesting significant upside potential. However, it’s worth remembering that analysts rarely issue sell ratings, partly because their firms often seek other business from the same companies they cover.
